Some suppliers, such as British Gas, EDF and E.ON have set up trusts and funds to help those struggling to pay their bills. Customers with electric-powered medical equipment at home can apply for rebates. And some disabled people may be eligible for Warm Home Discounts, Cold Weather Payments and Winter Fuel payments. But Andrew Long, of comparison site Switchcraft, said: “It’s a series of sticking plasters that don’t come close to matching the scale of the cost-of-living crisis.” For more on help for disabled people, visit Scope.org.uk